title: Tyson Foods Recalls Frozen Popcorn Chicken Products Due To Possible Foreign Matter Contamination
summary: WASHINGTON, Oct. 15, 2016 Tyson Foods, a New Holland, Pa. establishment, is recalling approximately 1,148 pounds of frozen popcorn chicken products that may be contaminated with extraneous materials, specifically hard plastic, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.The frozen...
